HOUSE RESOLUTION 187
By Todd
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Mickie Whitaker for her
distinguished service to mental health advocacy.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body take great pleasure in recognizing
those individuals who have devoted their lives to the service of others; and
WHEREAS, Mickie Whitaker is one such exemplary individual, whose decades of
selfless service and unwavering dedication to mental health advocacy have made a lasting
impact upon the citizens of Madison County and the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Whitaker began her journey with the National Alliance on Mental
Illness (NAMI) in the early 1990s, following her son's diagnosis with schizophrenia; rather than
yielding to uncertainty or fear, she sought out knowledge, support, and community, transforming
her personal experience into a lifelong mission of service; and
WHEREAS, through her involvement with NAMI Madison County in Jackson, Mickie
Whitaker became a dedicated educator in the organization's Family Education Program,
equipping families with essential tools and understanding to support loved ones living with
mental illness; and
WHEREAS, she later expanded her service to become a trainer, empowering others to
teach and to extend the reach of NAMI's programs throughout the region; and
WHEREAS, as one of the early grassroots leaders working to establish and strengthen
NAMI Tennessee, Mrs. Whitaker helped lay the foundation for a more informed, compassionate,
and supportive network of mental health advocacy across the State; and
WHEREAS, even while raising four children and supporting her family, Mickie Whitaker
has remained steadfast in her service, continuing to advocate for mental health awareness,
