- 1 -

encourage community engagement, and promote the vital mission of NAMI, particularly in areas
where awareness remains limited; and
WHEREAS, it is wholly fitting that we specially recognize Mickie Whitaker for her
outstanding service to mental health advocacy and enduring commitment to the well-being of
others; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
commend Mickie Whitaker for her exemplary service to mental health advocacy, extend to her
our sincere appreciation for her many contributions to the people of Tennessee, and wish her
every continued success and happiness in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
